reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great construction for several uses
reviews.reviewText: I really like these protectors. We use them to store recipes, articles and important documents. They are sturdy and fit really well in square storage boxes (think milk crate). I stack them in and can fit lots of them perfectly in the container. This helps me keep them organized. I am able to fit up to 35 sheets of paper with no problem.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just what I needed!
reviews.reviewText: Perfect. Lightweight, sturdy, see-through and different colors. They really help me keep organized.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Thick, Good Material
reviews.reviewText: These are almost exactly like what I have owned. Thick, and easy to use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars What's To Say? These things do the job and feel great in the hand.
reviews.reviewText: It's hard to say something about a product which one can tell by sight will do the job. They do. I'll add that they feel good. They slide easily which makes shuffling them around actually easier than with cardboard folders and the colors help identify different topic categories. I especially like being able to see the contents inside which saves me the trouble of labelling as one has to do with cardboard folders. I can SEE the topic. Actually two topics since I often put different related sources back to back inside and can just see the two different content types easily. I've bought these things more than once. They are good.
